WEBVTT

00:00.731 --> 00:02.673
HEY, YOU GUYS. GUESS WHAT.

00:02.673 --> 00:04.675
MY BOYFRIEND SMITH
FINISHED LAW SCHOOL.

00:04.675 --> 00:07.508
(singsongy)
HE COMES HOME TODAY.
WOW. THAT IS SO...

00:07.508 --> 00:10.181
JULES, WHAT'S THE WORD
FOR "WHO CARES?"

00:10.181 --> 00:13.184
ELLIE TORRES, I OPENED
MY BEST BOTTLE OF WINE FOR YOU

00:13.184 --> 00:16.187
LAST NIGHT, AND YOU LEFT A SIP.
I WOULD NEVER.

00:16.187 --> 00:17.718
THIS IS YOUR LIPSTICK.

00:17.718 --> 00:19.750
(singsongy) WINO FIGHT.
THAT WAS MY GLASS.

00:19.750 --> 00:22.493
I ACCIDENTALLY WORE
COLORED LIP BALM YESTERDAY.

00:22.493 --> 00:26.157
IT'S BARELY COLORED,
AND IT MAKES MY EYES POP.

00:26.157 --> 00:28.629
THAT'S HOW IT STARTED
FOR MY UNCLE MAX.

00:28.629 --> 00:32.163
THEN HE BOUGHT SOME WIGS
AND CHANGED HIS NAME TO MAXINE.

00:32.163 --> 00:35.206
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT'S REALLY
FUNNY? HE STILL GOES BY "MAX."

00:35.206 --> 00:38.069
"WHO CARES?" "WHO CARES?" WAS
THE WORD I WAS LOOKING FOR.

00:38.069 --> 00:40.040
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M GONNA DRINK IT.

00:40.040 --> 00:42.273
IT'S 8:00 A.M. ON A SATURDAY.

00:42.273 --> 00:45.276
SO? THIS IS JUST LIKE A MIMOSA,
EXCEPT FOR IT'S GOT WINE

00:45.276 --> 00:47.047
INSTEAD OF CHAMPAGNE
AND NO ORANGE JUICE.

00:47.047 --> 00:50.181
SOUNDS DELICIOUS.
MMM!

00:50.181 --> 00:53.053
WINE IN THE MORNING
ON THE WEEKENDS.
(door opens and closes)

00:53.053 --> 00:56.056
LET'S ALL THINK ABOUT IT,
PEOPLE.
THINK ABOUT WHAT?

00:56.056 --> 00:59.059
MORNING DRINKING.
FOR IT.
JULES, I GRABBED YOUR MAIL,

00:59.059 --> 01:01.332
AND TRAVIS GOT
HIS FIRST COLLEGE LETTER.

01:01.332 --> 01:03.664
IT'S FROM HIS SAFETY SCHOOL.

01:03.664 --> 01:05.666
BIG ENVELOPE.
(singsongy) HE GOT IN.

01:05.666 --> 01:08.399
TRAVIS, HELP! I'M HURT!

01:08.399 --> 01:11.142
OTHERWISE IT TAKES HIM FOREVER
TO COME DOWNSTAIRS.

01:11.142 --> 01:13.144
OKAY, I DON'T WANT
TO CALL FAVORITES,

01:13.144 --> 01:16.277
BUT HERE'S THE HUG ORDER--
ME, THEN BOBBY, THEN ME AGAIN

01:16.277 --> 01:19.650
AND THEN, YOU KNOW, WHATEVER.

01:19.650 --> 01:22.783
OH, GOOD. YOU'RE OKAY.

01:22.783 --> 01:25.486
WHOA.

01:25.486 --> 01:26.717
OKAY.

01:26.717 --> 01:28.259
HERE WE GO.

01:28.259 --> 01:33.093
EVERYBODY SAID THAT I SHOULD
GET THE FIRST HUG, RIGHT?

01:33.093 --> 01:35.726
THEY REJECTED ME.

01:35.726 --> 01:38.098
WELL,
I GUESS THESE SHOULD PROBABLY

01:38.098 --> 01:40.501
GO BACK
IN THEIR HOLSTERS.

01:46.137 --> 01:49.480
I FORGOT HOW SMOOTH
YOUR TEETH ARE.

01:49.480 --> 01:51.782
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HOME, TOO,
SON.

01:51.782 --> 01:54.785
FORGIVE ME
IF I DON'T EAT YOUR FACE.
I'M SORRY.
IT'S JUST--I HAVE A RULE

01:54.785 --> 01:57.418
THAT EVERY KISS MUST LAST
AT LEAST THREE SECONDS.

01:57.418 --> 02:01.222
IT'S WHAT THE OBAMAS DO.

02:01.222 --> 02:04.195
ANYWAY, TO CELEBRATE, I THOUGHT
THAT WE MIGHT GOLF TOGETHER.

02:04.195 --> 02:06.557
I HAVE A NEW PRO.
I'M AMAZING NOW.

02:06.557 --> 02:09.800
DOUBT IT, BUT I'M IN.
WELL, THANK YOU. I KNOW
YOU PREFER TO SPEND YOUR TIME

02:09.800 --> 02:11.902
LETTING HER TRY
TO TRICK A BABY OUT OF YOU.

02:11.902 --> 02:14.205
DAD, PLEASE JUST--

02:14.205 --> 02:17.568
I'M ALLERGIC TO LATEX
AND BIRTH CONTROL PILLS.

02:17.568 --> 02:19.139
NOT HELPING, BABE.

02:21.642 --> 02:23.143
SERIOUSLY?

02:23.143 --> 02:24.715
FEET OFF THE FURNITURE

02:24.715 --> 02:27.178
AND PICK UP ALL THIS KETTLE CORN
THAT YOU SPILLED.

02:27.178 --> 02:30.881
(sucking)
WITH YOUR HANDS,
NOT YOUR MOUTH VACUUM.

02:30.881 --> 02:33.884
AND THE EASIEST THING--
DRINKS GO ON COASTERS.

02:33.884 --> 02:37.828
QUICK HYPOTHETICAL--WHAT IF I
WAS TO TELL YOU THAT I'M A MAN,

02:37.828 --> 02:40.931
AND I CAN PUT MY DRINK DOWN
WHEREVER THE HELL I WANT?

02:40.931 --> 02:44.265
STUPID HYPOTHETICAL.

02:44.265 --> 02:48.369
(car alarm chirps,
dog barks in distance)
YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE TO HAVE
NO SAY IN YOUR OWN HOME?

02:48.369 --> 02:51.171
WE BOTH LIVE ALONE.
WE CAN DO WHATEVER WE WANT.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.674
(chuckles) I CAN PUT ON
MY OLD JEANS FROM HIGH SCHOOL

02:53.674 --> 02:56.207
AND ROCK OUT TO ENYA
IF I WANT TO.

02:56.207 --> 02:57.608
THAT'S... REALLY SPECIFIC.

02:57.608 --> 02:59.810
WHEN MY WIFE WAS AROUND,
THE ONLY TIME

02:59.810 --> 03:03.183
I HAD THE PLACE TO MYSELF WAS
AFTER SHE WENT TO BED.

03:03.183 --> 03:07.458
AND I'D WANDER AROUND
IN MY UNDERWEAR AND COWBOY HAT.
I HAVE SEVERAL COWBOY HATS.

03:07.458 --> 03:09.720
WELL, I HAVEN'T HAD
TO ANSWER TO ANYBODY

03:09.720 --> 03:13.564
SINCE SHARON DIED OF CANCER.
YOU'RE SO LUCKY.

03:13.564 --> 03:16.196
I-I JUST MEANT...

03:16.196 --> 03:18.229
MNH-MNH.
THERE'S NO SAVING THAT.

03:18.229 --> 03:19.730
(clink)
I'M LOVING THIS.

03:19.730 --> 03:21.302
ME, TOO.
(laughs)

03:21.302 --> 03:24.305
MMM. WHAT?

03:24.305 --> 03:26.477
IT'S 8:00 IN THE MORNING.
WE'RE TRYIN' SOMETHIN'.

03:26.477 --> 03:29.640
IT'S EUROPEAN.
WE DON'T ANSWER TO YOU.

03:29.640 --> 03:32.943
HOW YOU HOLDING UP THERE,
HONEY?
IT DOESN'T FEEL GREAT TO GET
TURNED DOWN BY A SCHOOL

03:32.943 --> 03:36.216
WITH FOUR GRAMMATICAL ERRORS
IN THEIR REJECTION LETTER.

03:36.216 --> 03:38.989
YOU KNOW,
I GOT INTO THAT SCHOOL.
COOL. KILL ME.

03:38.989 --> 03:40.991
I-I KNOW IT WAS
YOUR SAFETY SCHOOL,

03:40.991 --> 03:43.994
BUT YOU APPLIED
TO PLENTY OF OTHER COLLEGES.
TWO.

03:43.994 --> 03:47.958
PERFECT NUMBER. TRUST ME,
YOU HAVE NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.
THANK YOU FOR SAYING THAT.

03:47.958 --> 03:51.702
WELL, I'M SPEAKING THE TRUTH.
YOU'RE A HOME RUN HITTER!

03:51.702 --> 03:53.934
HE'S NOT.
OUR SON'S NOT GOING TO COLLEGE.

03:53.934 --> 03:55.666
THIS IS A DISASTER.

03:55.666 --> 03:58.369
NO, IT IS NOT. ALL RIGHT,
I NEVER FINISHED COLLEGE,

03:58.369 --> 04:00.771
AND LOOK AT ME.
I ENDED UP JUST...

04:00.771 --> 04:03.013
MORE WINE?

04:03.013 --> 04:05.316
FILL HER UP.
YES.

04:05.316 --> 04:09.249
OH, NO. YOU SEE
THAT GUY OVER THERE?

04:09.249 --> 04:11.021
JULES!
DON'T LOOK RIGHT AT HIM.

04:11.021 --> 04:14.385
I SAID, DON'T LOOK!
WHEN I HEAR "DON'T LOOK,"
I CAN'T HELP BUT LOOK.

04:14.385 --> 04:16.487
IT'S MY MOST SPECIFIC REFLEX.

04:16.487 --> 04:19.890
SMITH, REMEMBER WHEN WE MET
AND YOU WENT OFF TO LAW SCHOOL,

04:19.890 --> 04:21.892
WE ROLLED AROUND
WITH OTHER PEOPLE

04:21.892 --> 04:23.894
AND OCCASIONALLY HAD
MEDIOCRE PHONE SEX?

04:23.894 --> 04:27.998
YEAH,
IT WAS LIKE A FAIRY TALE.
HE'S ONE
OF MY ROLL-AROUND GUYS.

04:27.998 --> 04:30.000
JULES, DON'T LOOK. (laughs)

04:30.000 --> 04:32.373
OKAY, STOP IT.

04:32.373 --> 04:34.975
I CAN'T. IT'S TOO FUN.

04:34.975 --> 04:37.978
SMITH, MOST GUYS THAT I'VE DATED
WOULD GO OVER THERE

04:37.978 --> 04:40.751
AND MAKE A HUGE SCENE
AND BEAT THE CRAP OUT OF HIM

04:40.751 --> 04:43.984
WITH HIS WALLET CHAIN.
BUT DON'T FREAK OUT, OKAY?

04:43.984 --> 04:46.457
NO PROBLEM.

04:46.457 --> 04:48.859
MWAH.

04:48.859 --> 04:50.591
I'M DUMPING SMITH.

04:50.591 --> 04:52.292
AND THERE IT IS.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.994
(alarm beeps)

